rdf:Description.dc:title: FRAD model
rdf:Description.skos:note: This is the element set of native RDF classes and properties described in the Functional Requirements for Authority Data model. The model also uses elements previously described in the Functional Requirements for Bibliographic Records (FRBR) entity-relationship model.

rdf:Description.reg:name: Agency
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agency
rdf:Description.skos:definition: An organization responsible for creating or modifying a controlled access point. The agency is responsible for application and interpretation of the rules it creates and/or uses. The agency may also be responsible for the creation and maintenance of identifiers within its domain.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes libraries, national bibliographic agencies, bibliographic utilities, consortia, museums, archives, rights management organizations, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agencia

rdf:Description.reg:name: BibliographicEntity
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bibliographic Entity
rdf:Description.skos:definition: An entity which reflects intellectual constructs or concepts that are integral to the rules used to create library catalogues.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: What is perceived as a specific instance of a particular entity type may vary from one set of rules to another.

rdf:Description.reg:name: ControlledAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Controlled Access Point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A name, term, code, etc., under which a bibliographic or authority record or reference will be found.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Description is modified from: Guidelines for authority records and references / revised by the Working Group on GARE Revision. Second edition. München : K.G. Saur, 2001.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes access points designated as authorized (or preferred) forms of names (i.e., authorized access points) as well as those designated as variant forms of name (i.e., variant access points). Includes access points based on personal, family, and corporate names. Includes access points based on titles (i.e., names) for works, expressions, manifestations, and items. Includes access points consisting of a combination of two access points, as in the case of a creator/title access point for a work which consists of an authorized access point for the name of the creator combined with an authorized access point for the name (i.e., the title) of the work. Includes access points based on names and terms for events, objects, concepts, and places. Includes access points based on identifiers, such as standard numbers, classification indicia. Elements added to the name per se (e.g., dates) form an integral part of the controlled access point.

rdf:Description.reg:name: CorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Corporate Body
rdf:Description.skos:definition: An organization or group of persons and/or organizations identified by a particular name acting as a unit.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Description is modified from that in Functional requirements for bibliographic records : final report, by the IFLA Study Group on the Functional Requirements for Bibliographic Records, published by K.G. Saur, 1998.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes occasional groups and groups that are constituted as meetings, conferences, congresses, expeditions, exhibitions, festivals, fairs, etc. Includes musical performing groups, groups of visual artists, and dance companies producing collective work. Includes organizations that act as territorial authorities, exercising or claiming to exercise government functions over a certain territory, such as a federation, a state, a region, a local municipality. Includes organizations and groups that are defunct as well as those that continue to operate. Includes fictitious organizations or groups of persons.

rdf:Description.reg:name: Family
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Two or more persons related by birth, marriage, adoption, civil union, or similar legal status, or who otherwise present themselves as a family.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes royal families, dynasties, houses of nobility, etc. Includes patriarchies and matriarchies. Includes groups of individuals sharing a common ancestral lineage. Includes family units (parents, children, grandchildren, etc.). Includes the successive holders of a title in a house of nobility, viewed collectively (e.g., Dukes of Norfolk).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Familia

rdf:Description.reg:name: Identifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Identifier
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A number, code, word, phrase, logo, device, etc., that is associated with an entity, and serves to differentiate that entity from other entities within the domain in which the identifier is assigned. An identifier can consist of an identifier string (i.e., a sequence of numeric and/or alphabetic characters assigned to an entity to serve as a unique identifier within the domain to which the identifier is assigned) and a prefix and/or suffix (a character or set of characters (numeric and/or alphabetic) appearing before or after an identifier string).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes identifiers such as social insurance numbers assigned by a government authority. Includes personal identifiers assigned by other registration authorities. Includes business registration numbers, registration numbers for charitable organizations, etc., assigned by a government authority. Includes corporate body identifiers assigned by other registration authorities (e.g., ISBN publisher’s prefix). Includes standard identifiers assigned by registration authorities identifying content (e.g., ISRC, ISWC, ISAN). Includes standard identifiers assigned by registration authorities identifying manifestations (e.g., ISBN, ISSN). Includes thematic index numbers assigned to a musical work by the publisher, or a musicologist. Includes catalogue raisonné numbers. Includes identifiers for items assigned by repositories (e.g., shelf number). Includes classification numbers referencing specific entities (e.g., a classification number assigned to a particular painting). Includes registered trademarks.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Identificador

rdf:Description.reg:name: Name
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A character, word, or group of words and/or characters by which an entity is known.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes names by which persons, families, and corporate bodies are known. Includes titles by which works, expressions, and manifestations are known. Includes names and terms by which concepts, objects, events, and places are known. Includes real names, pseudonyms, religious names, initials, and separate letters, numerals, or symbols. Includes forenames (or given names), matronymics, patronymics, family names (or surnames), dynastic names, etc. Includes given names of sovereigns, popes, etc., with associated roman numerals. Includes names of families, clans, dynasties, houses of nobility, etc. Includes names representing the successive holders of a title in houses of nobility, etc., viewed collectively (e.g., Dukes of Norfolk). Includes names used by a corporate body at various periods in its history. Includes names of associations, institutions, business firms, not-for-profit enterprises, etc. Includes names of governments, government agencies, projects, programmes, government officials, delegations, legislative bodies, armed forces, etc. Includes names of religious bodies, local churches, etc., religious councils, religious officials, provinces, dioceses, synods, etc., papal diplomatic missions, etc. Includes names of conferences, congresses, meetings, etc. Includes names of exhibitions, athletic contests, expeditions, fairs, festivals, etc. Includes names of subordinate and related bodies. Includes numbers that form an integral part of the name of a corporate body or event. Includes trade names. Includes titles of content, parts of content, compilations of content, etc. Includes titles by which a work has become known. Includes the title proper of the original manifestation of a work. Includes titles by which a work is identified in reference sources. Includes titles under which a work has been published. Includes titles by which manifestations of an expression have become known. Includes the title proper of the original manifestation of an expression. Includes titles by which manifestations of an expression are identified in reference sources. Includes titles under which manifestations of an expression have been published. Includes the title proper of the original edition of a manifestation. Includes titles by which a manifestation is identified in reference sources. Includes variant titles appearing on or in a manifestation. Includes names and terms for events, objects, concepts, and places.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Nombre

rdf:Description.reg:name: NameOfACorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Name of a Corporate Body
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A name which is the appellation of a corporate body.

rdf:Description.reg:name: NameOfAFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Name of a Family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A name which is the appellation of a family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: NameOfAPerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Name of a Person
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A name which is the appellation of a person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: NameOfAWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Name of a Work
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A name which is the appellation of a work.

rdf:Description.reg:name: Rules
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rules
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A set of instructions relating to the formulation and/or recording of controlled access points (authorized forms, variant forms or references, etc.).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes cataloguing rules and interpretations of those rules. Includes coding conventions.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Reglas

rdf:Description.reg:name: applies
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: applies
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an agency to rules that it applies when creating or modifying a controlled access point.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: aplica

rdf:Description.reg:name: areAppliedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: are applied by
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates rules to an agency that applies them when creating or modifying a controlled access point.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: son aplicadas por

rdf:Description.reg:name: creates
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: creates
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an agency to a controlled access point that is created by the agency.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: crea

rdf:Description.reg:name: govern
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: govern
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates rules to a controlled access point that they govern.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: regula

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAccompanyingRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has accompanying relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to another work that is a supplement to that work (i.e., a work that is intended to be used in conjunction with or to augment the related work, such as a teacher’s guide or incidental music to a play; or intended to complement or be a companion to another work, such as a set of maps to a video travelogue, a computer disk to accompany a textbook, a set of coloured plates to accompany a text, the equal parts of a kit).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAcronymOrInitialsOrAbbreviation
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has acronym or initials or abbreviation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a corporate body and an acronym or initials or an abbreviation by which that body is known.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene acrónimo o iniciales o abreviaturas

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAddition
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has addition
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to a name, title, date, place, number, or other designation added to the base access point.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes the fuller form of name added to the base access point. Includes the title of nobility, title of royalty, or ecclesiastical title added to the base access point. Includes dates added to the base access point. Includes the place name associated with a corporate body added to the base access point. Includes a number associated with a corporate body or a musical work added to the base access point. Includes a title of an adaptation or version of a work added to the base access point. Includes the name and/or number of a section or part of a work added to the base access point. Includes a term designating the form of a work added to the base access point. Includes a term designating language of expression added to the base access point. Includes a term designating the key in which a musical work was originally composed added to the base access point. Includes a term designating the medium of performance for which a musical work was originally conceived added to the base access point. Includes other designations associated with persons and corporate bodies added to the base access point.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene adición

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAddressCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has address (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to the current or former address of the corporate body's office(s).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes addresses for the corporate body's headquarters and/or other offices. Includes street address, postal address, telephone number, e-mail address, etc. Includes the address of a World Wide Web site operated by the corporate body, about the corporate body or related to the corporate body.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAddressPerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has address (person)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to the current or former address of the person's place of residence, business, or employer.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes street address, postal address, telephone number, e-mail address, etc. Includes the address of a World Wide Web site operated by the person, about the person or related to the person.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene dirección (persona)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAffiliation
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has affiliation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a group with which the person is affiliated or has been affiliated through employment, membership, cultural identity, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene afiliación

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAlternateScriptForm
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has alternate script form
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates controlled access points that are established as alternate script forms of the access point for the authorized forms of name for the same entity.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAlternativeLinguisticFormCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has alternative linguistic form (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a corporate body and an alternative linguistic form of name by which that body is known.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes translations of the name for the corporate body.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene forma lingüística alternativa (entidad corporativa)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAlternativeLinguisticFormFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has alternative linguistic form (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a family and an alternative linguistic form of name by which that family is known.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene forma lingüística alternativa (familia)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAlternativeLinguisticFormPerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has alternative linguistic form (person)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a person and an alternative linguistic form of name by which that person is known.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes translations of a name into other languages.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene forma lingüística alternativa (persona)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAlternativeLinguisticFormWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has alternative linguistic form (work)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a work and an alternative linguistic form of name by which that work is known.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene forma lingüística alternativa (obra)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAppellation
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has appellation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a bibliographic entity to a name.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAsSubjectFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has as subject (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to a family that is the subject of the work.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene como materia (familia)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasAttributedWorksFrom
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has attributed works from
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person (either a "real" individual or a persona) or identity to whom one or more works by another person have been attributed, either erroneously or falsely, and that other person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasBaseAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has base access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to all elements in a controlled access point that are integral to the name or identifier that forms the basis for the access point.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes the name element in a controlled access point beginning with the name of a person, family, or corporate body. Includes the phrase element in a controlled access point beginning with a phrase associated with a person that is used in lieu of a name as such when the name of the person is unknown (e.g., A Physician, Author of Early Impressions). Includes the name element for a subordinate or related body in a controlled access point beginning with the name of a superior body. Includes the name element for a government agency, official, legislative body, court, etc., in a controlled access point beginning with the name for the territorial authority. Includes the name element for a religious council, official, province, synod, etc., in a controlled access point beginning with the name for the religious body. Includes the title element in a controlled access point for a work. Includes a term designating form at the beginning of the title element of a controlled access point for a musical work or expression (e.g., Symphony, Concerto). Includes conventional and collective titles at the beginning of the title element of a controlled access point for a work or expression (e.g., Treaties, Laws, Works, Selections, Piano music). Includes the additional element(s) in a collective title controlled access point (i.e., a subsequent term or terms used to subdivide the collective uniform title)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasBiographyOrHistory
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has biography or history
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to information pertaining to the life or history of the person.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene biografía o historia

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasChild
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has child
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to another person who is a "child" of that person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasCitationForRules
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has citation for rules
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates rules to a citation for the cataloguing code, set of rules, instructions, etc.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes the title of the rules, etc., and, as necessary, the name of the body responsible for the rules, the edition designation, date, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene cita de reglas

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasCollaborativeRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has collaborative relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two persons (i.e., individuals) who collaborate in intellectual or artistic endeavours
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene relación colaborativa con

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasConventionalName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has conventional name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a work and a conventional name by which that work is known
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene nombre convencional

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasCorrespondingSubjectTermOrClassificationNumber
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has corresponding subject term or classification number
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point for the name of a bibliographic entity and a subject term in a controlled vocabulary or a classification number for that entity.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: The subject term and the classification number may also be viewed as parallel names or identifiers for the name of the same entity.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasCountry
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has country
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a country with which the person is identified.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene país

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasCustodialHistoryOfItem
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has custodial history of item
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an item to the record of previous ownership of an item.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDatesOfFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has dates of family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to dates associated with the family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDatesOfUsage
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has dates of usage
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to dates associated with the use of a particular name established by a person, corporate body, or family.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene fechas de uso

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDerivative
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has derivative
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to another work which is an adaptation or modification of the prior work.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes relationships between an original work and a broad range of modifications from the original, including variations or versions of that work, such as editions, revisions, translations, summaries, abstracts, and digests. Includes new works that are adaptations or modifications that become new works but are based on an earlier work (improvisations, etc.); new works that are changes of genre (transformations, dramatizations, novelizations, etc.); and, new works based on the style or thematic content of other works (free translations, paraphrases, imitations, parodies, etc.).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene derivada

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDescendentGenealogicalRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has (descendent) genealogical relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to another family that descended from the prior family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDescriptiveWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has descriptive work
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a target work or expression or manifestation or item and a new work that refers to that target as its subject.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes criticism, commentary, review, casebook, etc., and the object of that analysis (that is, the target work, expression, or manifestation).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene obra descriptiva

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDesignatedUsageOfControlledAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has designated usage of controlled access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an indication of whether the rules under which the controlled access point was constructed designate it as an authorized (or preferred) form (i.e., authorized access point) or as a variant (or non-preferred) form (i.e., variant access points).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasDifferentRulesForm
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has different rules form
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates controlled access points for the authorized forms of name for the same entity that have been established according to different sets of rules.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasEarlierName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has earlier name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a person to a name that person used at an earlier stage in life.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene nombre anterior

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasEquivalenceItemRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has equivalence (item) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an item to another item that exemplifies the same intellectual or artistic content (work or work-expression).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasEquivalenceManifestationRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has equivalence (manifestation) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a manifestation to another manifestation that embodies the same intellectual or artistic content (work or work-expression).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasExpandedName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has expanded name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a corporate body and the expanded form of name by which that body is known.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene nombre extenso

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasFieldOfActivityCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has field of activity (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to a field of business in which the corporate body is engaged, its area of competence, responsibility, jurisdiction, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene campo de actividad (entidad corporativa)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasFieldOfActivityFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has field of activity (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to afield of endeavour, area of expertise, etc., in which the family is engaged or was engaged.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene campo de actividad (familia)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasFieldOfActivityPerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has field of activity (person)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a field of endeavour, area of expertise, etc., in which the person is engaged or was engaged.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene campo de actividad (persona)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasFounder
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has founder
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to a family which created it.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasGender
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has gender
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a gender by which the person is identified.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: E.g., male, female, unknown, other.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene género

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasHistoryCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has history (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to information pertaining to the history of the corporate body.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes historical information pertaining to an organization, institution, etc.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasHistoryOfFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has history of family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to information pertaining to the history of the family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasHistoryWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has history (work)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to information pertaining to the history of the work.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes historical information pertaining to a work, including title changes for continuing resources.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene historia (obra)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasImmediateSourceOfAcquisitionOfItem
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has immediate source of acquisition of item
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an item to the source from which an item was directly acquired and the circumstances under which it was acquired.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfBaseAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of base access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the language in which the base access point is recorded.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfCataloguing
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of cataloguing
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the language in which additions to the base access point are recorded.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene lengua de catalogación

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to a language associated with the family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to the language in which the name is expressed.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfPerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of person
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a language the person uses when creating an expression for publication, broadcasting, etc.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLanguageOfTheCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has language of the corporate body
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to a language that the corporate body uses in its communications.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLaterName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has later name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a person and a name that person used at a later stage in life.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene nombre posterior

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasLocationOfItem
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has location of item
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an item to the collection and/or institution in which the item is held, stored, or made available for access.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Scope note not present in original documentation; added to clarify semantic difference with "is part (item)" property (http://iflastandards.info/ns/fr/frbr/frbrer/P2092).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: E.g. Moir rare book collection, http://www.juilliardmanuscriptcollection.org/, Short loan collection (School of African and Oriental Studies, University of London), Library of Congress. Does not include collections where the item is originally published or manufactured as a component part.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasMemberCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has member (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to a person who is a member of or affiliated with the corporate body.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasMemberFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has member (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to a person who is a member of the family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasNameString
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has name string
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to a sequence of numeric and/or alphabetic characters or symbols that represents the name of an entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene cadena de caracteres

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasNumericDesignation
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has numeric designation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to a number assigned to it.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes serial numbers, opus numbers assigned by the composer of a musical work, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene designación numérica

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasOfficialIdentity
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has official identity
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person and an identity that person assumes in an official capacity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene identidad oficial

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasOtherVariantNameCorporateBody
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has other variant name (corporate body)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a corporate body and a name by which that body is known (other than expanded name, acronym, initials, abbreviation, and alternative linguistic form).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes orthographic variant names (spelling variations, transliterations, punctuation variations, capitalization variations), word order variant names (inversions, permutations).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasOtherVariantNamePerson
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has other variant name (person)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a person and several other variations on a name (other than earlier name, later name, and alternative linguistic form).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes orthographic variant names (spelling variations, transliterations, punctuation variations, capitalization variations), word order variant names (inversions, permutations), alternative name/synonym variant names (bynames, nicknames, courtesy names).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasOtherVariantNameWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has other variant name (work)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name of a work and a name by which that work is known (other than conventional name, and alternative linguistic form).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes orthographic variant names(spelling variations, transliterations, punctuation variations, capitalization variations), word order variant names(inversions, permutations), variant title variant names (titles for the work based on titles found on manifestations or items, including cover title, spine title, caption title, container title, parallel title).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasOwner
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has owner
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to a family which owns it.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene propietario

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasParallelLanguageForm
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has parallel language form
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates controlled access points that are established as parallel language forms of access point for the authorized forms of name for the same entity.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasParent
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has parent
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to another person who is a “parent” of that person.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has parent
rdf:Description.reg:name: hasParent
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to another person who is a "parent" of that person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPlaceOfBirth
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has place of birth
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to the town, city, province, state, and/or country in which the person was born.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene lugar de nacimiento

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPlaceOfDeath
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has place of death
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to the town, city, province, state, and/or country in which the person died.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene lugar de fallecimiento

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPlaceOfOriginOfTheWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has place of origin of the work
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to the country or other territorial jurisdiction or cultural area from which the work originated.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes area of origin, etc.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene lugar de origen de la obra

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPlaceOfResidence
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has place of residence
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a country, state/province, city, etc., in which the person resides or has resided.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene lugar de residencia

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPlacesAssociatedWithFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has places associated with family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to information pertaining to places where the family resides or resided or had some connection.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPredecessorGenealogicalRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has (predecessor) genealogical relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to another family which is the precursor of the prior family.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasProfessionOrOccupation
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has profession or occupation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person to a profession or occupation in which the person works or worked.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasPseudonymousPersona
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has pseudonymous persona
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a "real" person (i.e., an individual) and a persona(ae) or identity adopted by that individual through the use of one or more pseudonyms.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasRelatedIdentifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has related identifier
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point based on an authorized or variant form of name of a bibliographic entity to an identifier for the same bibliographic entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene identificador relacionado

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasReligiousIdentity
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has religious identity
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person and an identity that person assumes in a religious capacity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene identidad religiosa

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasRulesIdentifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has rules identifier
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates rules to an acronym or initials or alphanumeric code identifying the rules.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene identificador de reglas

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasScopeOfUsage
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has scope of usage
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to the form of work associated with a particular name for a persona.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes forms, genres, etc., (e.g., literary works, critical works, works on mathematics, detective novels) associated with a name used by an author.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene alcance de uso

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasScriptOfBaseAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has script of base access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the form of graphic characters in which the data in the base access point are recorded.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasScriptOfCataloguing
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has script of cataloguing
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the form of graphic characters in which any additions to the base access point are recorded.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasScriptOfName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has script of name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to the script in which the name is rendered

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSecularIdentity
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has secular identity
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person and an identity that person assumes in a secular capacity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene identidad secular

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSequentialRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has sequential relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to another work of different content that is a successor or a predecessor of that work,
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: E.g. a sequel, a serial or series that has changed title. Excludes derivative works that modify the content of an earlier work.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSharedCharacteristicExpressionRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has shared characteristic (expression) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two expressions that have some characteristic in common.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Excludes specific characteristics represented by other properties.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene relación de característica compartida (expresión)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSharedCharacteristicItemRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has shared characteristic (item) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two items that have some characteristic in common.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Excludes specific characteristics represented by other properties.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene relación de característica compartida (ejemplar)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSharedCharacteristicManifestationRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has shared characteristic (manifestation) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two manifestations that have some characteristic in common.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Excludes specific characteristics represented by other properties.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene relación de característica compartida (manifestación)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSharedCharacteristicWorkRelationship
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has shared characteristic (work) relationship
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two works that have some characteristic in common.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Excludes specific characteristics represented by other properties.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene relación de característica compartida (obra)

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSibling
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has sibling
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two persons who have the same “parent(s)” (in an actual family or within a group).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has sibling
rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSibling
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates two persons who have the same "parent(s)" (in an actual family or within a group).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSourceOfControlledAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has source of controlled access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the publication or reference source used in establishing the form of name or title on which the controlled access point is based.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes the title, publisher, date, etc., of the resource for which the controlled access point was originally created. Includes the title, edition, etc., of the reference source(s) used to establish the conventional name or title.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasStatusOfControlledAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has status of controlled access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an indication of the level of establishment of the authorized access point for the entity (e.g., provisional).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSubjectOfTheWork
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has subject of the work
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to the subject aspects of the work and its content.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes information about the subject of the work. Includes classification numbers.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasSubordinate
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has subordinate
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to another corporate body which is subordinate to the prior corporate body.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene subordinado

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTransliterationSchemeOfBaseAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has transliteration scheme of base access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an indication of the scheme used in transliterating the base access point.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTransliterationSchemeOfCataloguing
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has transliteration scheme of cataloguing
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an indication of the scheme used in transliterating any additions to the base access point.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTransliterationSchemeOfName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has transliteration scheme of name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to the scheme used to produce the transliterated form of the name.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene esquema de transliteración del nombre

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTypeOfControlledAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has type of controlled access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to a categorization or generic descriptor for the controlled access point.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes terms and/or codes designating the type of access point (e.g., personal name access point, family name access point, corporate name access point, meeting name access point, territorial name access point, title access point, collective title access point or access points consisting of a combination of names, such as creator/title access points).

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTypeOfFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has type of family
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to a categorization or generic descriptor for the type of family.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes categorizations, such as clan, dynasty, family unit, patriarchy, matriarchy, etc.

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTypeOfIdentifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has type of identifier
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identifier to a code or other designation indicating the type of identifier (i.e., the domain in which the identifier is assigned).
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes alphabetic strings identifying the numbering system (e.g., "ISBN", "ISSN", "ISRC"). Includes symbols designating the type of identifier (e.g., registered trademark symbol)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene tipo de identificador

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasTypeOfName
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has type of name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to the category of a name.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes personal names, corporate names, names of families, trade names, and titles of works and manifestations. Includes names of concepts, objects, events, and places.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene tipo de nombre

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasUndifferentiatedAccessPoint
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has undifferentiated access point
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an indication that the controlled access point for the authorized form of name (i.e., authorized access point) is insufficiently precise to differentiate between two or more entities identified by the same name.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: tiene punto de acceso no diferenciado

rdf:Description.reg:name: hasWorksAttributedTo

rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates one person and another person (either a "real" individual or a persona) or identity to whom one or more works by the former have been attributed, either erroneously or falsely.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has works attributed to
rdf:Description.reg:name: hasWorksAttributedTo
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates one person and another person (either a "real" individual or a persona) or identity to whom one or more works by the former have been attributed, either erroneously or falsely.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isAppellationOf

rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to a bibliographic entity.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isAssigned

rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a bibliographic entity to an identifier assigned to the entity.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isAssignedTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is assigned to
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identifier to a bibliographic entity to which it is assigned.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isAssociatedWith
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is associated with
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a person, a family, or a corporate body to a work, expression, manifestation, or item.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isBasedOnIdentifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is based on (identifier)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to an identifier on which it is based.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: está basado en (identificador)

rdf:Description.reg:name: isBasedOnName

rdf:Description.reg:name: isBasisIdentifierFor

rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identifier to a controlled access point for which it is the basis.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isBasisNameFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is basis (name) for
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a name to a controlled access point for which it is the basis.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isConventionalNameOf

rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the agency that creates it.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es creado por

rdf:Description.reg:name: isCreatedByFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is created by (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to a family which is responsible for the creation of the intellectual or artistic content of the work.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es creada por (familia)

rdf:Description.reg:name: isCreatorFamilyOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is creator (family) of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to a work of which it is responsible for the creation of the intellectual or artistic content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es creadora (familia) de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isDerivativeOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is derivative of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a work to another work of which it is an adaptation or modification.
rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes relationships between an original work and a broad range of modifications from the original, including variations or versions of that work, such as editions, revisions, translations, summaries, abstracts, and digests. Includes new works that are adaptations or modifications that become new works but are based on an earlier work (improvisations, etc.); new works that are changes of genre (transformations, dramatizations, novelizations, etc.); and, new works based on the style or thematic content of other works (free translations, paraphrases, imitations, parodies, etc.).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es derivativa de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isDescriptiveWorkOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is descriptive work of

rdf:Description.skos:scopeNote: Includes criticism, commentary, review, casebook, etc., and the object of that analysis (that is, the target work, expression, or manifestation).

rdf:Description.reg:name: isFounderOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is founder of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to a corporate body which the family created.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es fundador de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isGovernedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is governed by
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a controlled access point to the rules that govern it.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es regulado por

rdf:Description.reg:name: isMemberOfCorporateBody

rdf:Description.reg:name: isMemberOfFamily

rdf:Description.reg:name: isModifiedBy

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es modificado por

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is official identity of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identity a person assumes in an official capacity and the person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isOwnedByFamily

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es propietario de

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es predecesora de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isProducedByFamily

rdf:Description.reg:name: isProducerFamilyOf

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es productora (familia) de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isPseudonymousPersonaOf

rdf:Description.reg:name: isRealizedByFamily
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is realized by (family)
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an expression to a family that is responsible for the specifics of the intellectual or artistic realization or execution of the expression.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es realizada por (familia)

rdf:Description.reg:name: isRealizerFamilyOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is realizer (family) of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a family to an expression of which it is responsible for the specifics of the intellectual or artistic realization or execution.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es realizadora (familia) de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isReligiousIdentityOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is religious identity of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identity a person assumes in a religious capacity and the person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isSecularIdentityOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is secular identity of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates an identity a person assumes in a secular capacity and the person.

rdf:Description.reg:name: isSubordinateOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is subordinate of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to another corporate body to which it is subordinate.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es subordinado de

rdf:Description.reg:name: isSuccessorOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is successor of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Relates a corporate body to another corporate body of which it is a successor.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: es sucesora de
